        THIS_IS_WINDURST_S_NORTH_AUCTION_HOUSE_WE                               = 7212,  -- This is Windurst's North Auction House. We can deliver your belongings to your home, or help you send presents to anyone in Vana'diel.
        OUR_PRICES_ARE_MOST_REASONABLE_THERE_S_NO                               = 7213,  -- Our prices are most reasonable. There's no greater joy than the joy of giving, so ask one of my pretty little assistants to arrange your deliveries.
        WE_ARE_THE_LOCAL_COURIER_WOURIERS_WE_DELIVER                            = 7214,  -- We are the local courier-wouriers. We deliver the goods that people leave with the girly-wirlies over therey-wherey.
        IF_YOU_WANTARU_PARTICIPATE_IN_THE_AUCTION_THEN                          = 7215,  -- If you wantaru participate in the auction, then step rightaru up to the counters lining the wall over there.
        WE_DELIVER_GOODY_WOODIES_TO_YOUR_HOME_OR                                = 7216,  -- We deliver goody-woodies to your home, or the home of one of your friendy-wiendies!
        I_CAN_ARRANGEY_DELIVERY_OF_YOUR_BELONGINGS_TO                           = 7217,  -- I can arrangey delivery of your belongings to your Mog Housey or Rent-a-Roomy for you.
        DID_YOU_HEAR_DID_YOU_HEAR_THE_AUCTIONEER                                = 7218,  -- Did you hear? Did you hear? The auctioneer over there--one of his deliverymen was attacked by a monster! What terribliociousness!
        GEE_AN_AUCTION_COURIER_IS_A_PRETTY_DANGEROUS                            = 7219,  -- Gee... An auction courier is a pretty dangerous job! It seems that every day you hear of another deliveryman getting attacked by some wild beasty-weasty or crazy customer.
        THIS_IS_THE_NORTH_AUCTION_HOUSE_WE_WOULD                                = 7220,  -- This is the North Auction House. We would like to transport your belongings to your home, or help you send presents to people...but...we're having problems delivering on that promise.
        ALAS_A_TERRIBLE_OCCURRENCE_HAS_BEFALLEN_US                              = 7221,  -- Alas... A terrible occurrence has befallen us.
        YOU_SEE_THE_OTHER_DAY_ONE_OF_MY                                         = 7222,  -- You see, the other day, one of my deliverymen was attacked by a monster. And...we seem to have lost several of the letters he was carrying.
        IF_I_DON_T_DO_SOMETHING_TO_RETRIEVE                                     = 7223,  -- If I don't do something to retrieve the mail and deliver it to its rightful owners, the reliable name of my courier service will be ruined! Dear adventurer, would you be so kind as to help us find our lost mail?
        HELP_FIND_MISSING_MAIL_YES_NO                                           = 7224,  -- Help find missing mail? Yes. No.
        I_SEE_GUESS_I_LL_HAVE_TO_ASK                                            = 7225,  -- I see... Guess I'll have to ask someone else. Oh, where's a decent adventurer when you need one!?
        THANK_YOU_THANK_YOU_OUR_DELIVERYMAN_WAS_AMBUSHED                        = 7226,  -- Thank you! Thank you! Our deliveryman was ambushed where the Tahrongi Canyon meets East Sarutabaruta.
        SO_IF_YOU_CAN_SEARCH_HIGH_AND_LOW                                       = 7227,  -- So if you can search high and low in both the Tahrongi Canyon and Sarutabaruta, hopefully you'll be able to find all the pieces of mail that were lost.
        PLEASE_BRING_ME_BACK_WHATEVER_YOU_CAN_FIND                              = 7228,  -- Please bring me back whatever you can find! Through rain and shine, monsters and beastmen, the mail must get through!
        SEEMS_THAT_ALL_OF_OUR_DELIVERYMEN_LET_DOWN                              = 7229,  -- Seems that all of our deliverymen let down their guard when crossing between the Tahrongi Canyon and East Sarutabaruta. They must think they can outrun the monsters there or something.
        ANYWAY_EVEN_IF_YOU_FIND_A_SINGLE_MISSING                                = 7230,  -- Anyway, even if you find a single missing item of mail, please bring it back to me. Through rain and shine, monsters and beastmen, the mail must get through!
        THE_LAST_TIME_SOMETHING_LIKE_THIS_HAPPENED_IT                           = 7231,  -- The last time something like this happened, it was the Savanna Rarabs that made off with most of our maily-waily. Seems they think they can make a comfy-womfy nest out of our letters.
