        BUT_THE_YAGUDO_DON_TARU_SEEM_THE_LEAST                                  = 7909,  -- But the Yagudo don'taru seem the least bit thankful. Annoying, isn'taru it?
        WHY_ARE_THERE_SO_MANY_HOT_BLOODED_MITHRA                                = 7910,  -- Why are there so many hot-blooded Mithra? They shouldn't worry so much about winning or losing-wosing.
        WHAT_S_DONE_IS_DONE_DON_T_YOU                                           = 7911,  -- What's done is done. Don't you think-wink that it's better to forget the past and concentrate on improving your relationships with others now?
        DOCTOR_SHANTOTTO_THE_FORMER_MINISTER_OF_THE_ORASTERY_2                  = 7912,  -- Doctor Shantotto, the former Minister of the Orastery, or Mage Academy, lives in this house here. I'm sure that she's hiding something-womething!
        WHO_AM_I_WELL_I_M_THE_REPORTER_2                                        = 7913,  -- Who am I? Well, I'm the reporter who's waiting to get a tell-all interview with her! You see, I write for the Tarutaru Times' Magic Paradise Weekly.
        THEY_SAY_OLD_DOC_SHANTOTTO_S_AS_HIGH_2                                  = 7914,  -- They say old Doc Shantotto's as high-and-mighty as Yutungah's firey mountain, and as rough-cut as the rocky Gustaberg Ranges-wanges.
        I_GUESS_IT_WAS_WRONG_OF_ME_TO                                           = 7915,  -- I guess it was wrong of me to start off by interviewing the people around her. The more I hear about the doctor, the less I want to meet her-wer.
        THAT_BUILDING_UP_THERE_O_ERE_IS_A                                       = 7916,  -- That building up there-o-ere is a foreign country's consulate. There is an agreement between Windurst and the other countries that they help each other out when they are in trouble-o-rouble.
        SO_I_DON_T_SEE_WHY_WE_NEED                                              = 7917,  -- So I don't see why we need-o-eed consulates or embassies. If someone is in trouble, we should be helping them out regardless of whether they are Windurstian or not-o-wot!
        I_FEEL_SO_SORRY_FOR_NASTY_OLD_ZONPA                                     = 7918,  -- I feel so sorry for nasty old Zonpa-Zippa's daughter, Miss Apururu. With a father like thaty-watty, not to mention that horrible-worrible brother of hers...! Well, it just goes to show that you suffer-wuffer your whole life when you come from a bad family.
        THE_PROFESSOR_THATARU_LIVED_IN_THIS_MANOR_WAS                           = 7919,  -- The professor thataru lived in this manor was kidnapped several years ago by those automaton guard creations of his that he named Cardians. No one's heard anything of him since the day he was spirited away.
        BUT_IT_SERVES_HIM_RIGHTARU_AS_THAT_PROFESSOR                            = 7920,  -- But it serves him rightaru, as that professor was the biggest liar Windurst ever knew. He's probably in the stomach of some nut-headed Cardian by now...or at leastaru one can hope.
        WE_LOST_ALL_TOO_MANY_WANY_LOVED_ONES                                    = 7921,  -- We lost all too many-wany loved ones during the Great War, two decades ago.
        HOWEVER_THE_GREAT_STAR_TREE_AND_THE_STAR                                = 7922,  -- However, the Great Star Tree and the Star Sibyl survived unharmed, so we Windurstians were able to rebuild our lives without losing all hopey-wopey.
        THE_STAR_TREE_IS_LIKE_A_GUARDIAN_ANGEL                                  = 7923,  -- The Star Tree is like a guardian angel-wangel, who, together with the Star Sibyl, looks after Windurst and the Tarutaru who dwell herey-werey.
        MY_HEART_FEELS_AT_PEACEY_WEACEY_WHENEVER_I                              = 7924,  -- My heart feels at peacey-weacey whenever I pray to the Great Star Tree, as I am doing now.
        HAVE_YOU_EVER_HEARD_WEARD_ABOUT_THE_GREAT                               = 7925,  -- Have you ever heard-weard about the great summoner, Karaha-Baruha, who saved Windurst twenty years back?
        SEE_THE_EMPTY_HOUSE_ON_THE_HILL_HERE                                    = 7926,  -- See the empty house on the hill here? That's the manor where the genius-wenius was supposed to live after he retired as Minister of the Optistery. The town's children think it's haunted-waunted and call it the ghosty house.
        WHATARU_DON_TARU_TELL_ME_SOMEONE_IS_SEARCHING                           = 7927,  -- Whataru? Don'taru tell me someone is searching for us already? Oh...? Phew...! Don'taru you dare tell head lady-in-waiting Zubaba about it, butaru, we sortaru of snuck outaru of Heavens Tower for a bitaru.
        LATELY_THE_STAR_SIBYL_S_DIVINATIONS_HAVE_BEEN                           = 7928,  -- Lately the Star Sibyl's divinations have been a little off the marky-warky. Of coursey-woursey, this has put the head lady-in-waiting in rather a bad mood, to say the leasty-weasty. It's simply dreadful-weadful!
        MY_DREAM_IS_TO_BECOME_A_LADY_IN                                         = 7929,  -- My dream is to become a lady-in-waiting and serve the Star Sibyl, but I keep getting turned down by the head lady-in-waiting every time I ask for an interview. How dare she keep me waiting like this with those silly excuses of hers!
        FLIBBERTIGIBBET_MY_WORD_WHAT_S_WRONG_WITH_A                             = 7930,  -- Flibbertigibbet, my word! What's wrong with a little gossiping, anyway? Actually, I think my spreading of information is a vital community service. Wouldn't you agree?
        GEE_MAY_THE_GODDESS_HELP_US_IF_A                                        = 7931,  -- Gee... May the Goddess help us if a gossiper-wossiper like Ms. Mehruru ever became-ewame a lady-in-waiting. There'd be no secrets-wecrets left in Heavens Tower-wower!
        THE_STAR_READING_CEREMONY_IS_A_SPECIAL_RITE                             = 7932,  -- The Star Reading ceremony is a special rite that entails the gathering of the five ministers and the Star Sibyl together to listen-wisten to the will of the stars in the skies above. The last Star Reading said that Windurst would have everlasting peace-weace.
        I_M_JUST_GLAD_WAD_WE_DIDN_T                                             = 7933,  -- I'm just glad-wad we didn't have an ill-boding omen come up, like the ones we got during the Great War twenty years ago.
        ITHN_T_IT_BIGGY_WIGGY_ITHN_T_IT                                         = 7934,  -- Ithn't it biggy-wiggy? Ithn't it hugey-wugey? Can you thee it? Can you thee it? That'th the Great Thtar Tree that grew-and-grew out of and all over Heaventh Tower!
        IT_GREW_THITH_BIG_THANKTH_TO_THE_MAGICAL                                = 7935,  -- It grew thith big thankth to the magical blething of the thtars in the thky! I with they would help me grow up big thoon too!
        SORRY_DORRY_I_M_IN_THE_MIDDLE_OF                                        = 7936,  -- Sorry-dorry! I'm in the middle of escorting a researcher from the Rhinostery's bio lab around here. But gee-weez, I sure wish he didn't have to come at such a busy time as this. <mumble-grumble>
        HMM_TSK_TSK_THIS_IS_MORE_SERIOUS_DERIOUS                                = 7937,  -- Hmm... Tsk-tsk... This is more serious-derious than I thought-dought...
        AH_OH_HUH_IF_YOU_RE_LOOKING_DOOKING                                     = 7938,  -- ...Ah? ...Oh! ...Huh? If you're looking-dooking for the entrance to Heavens Tower, it's on the other side-dide of this poor old star tree that encases it.
        AFTER_YEARS_OF_TRYING_I_WAS_FINALLY_GIVEN                               = 7939,  -- After years of trying, I was finally given the privilege of serving the Star Sibyl, but I gotaru fired for being too clumsy and a scatterbrain.
        NOW_I_DON_TARU_KNOW_WHATARU_TO_DO                                       = 7940,  -- Now I don'taru know whataru to do-woo! How can I ever face my mother and father, my brothers and sisters, or my grandfather or grandmother ever again? Oh, and then there's my cousins and my friends, and my family's friends, and their friends' friends and...
        COME_ON_PROFESSORRR_KORU_MORU_I_M_NOT                                   = 7941,  -- Come on, Professorrr Koru-Moru. I'm not moving until you cough up the gil forrr yourrr overdue accounts at the Boneworkers' Guild. As both a ministerrr and the principal of our local school, shouldn't you be setting a betterrr example?
        IF_YOU_NEED_TO_ENTER_HEAVENS_TOWER_THEN                                 = 7942,  -- If you need to enter Heavens Tower, then you'll have to crrross that bridge over there. Look around you, and you'll realize that the ruins of the once-grrreat walls of Windurst are prrractically filled with water.
        IT_WAS_TWENTY_YEARS_AGO_DURING_THE_GRRREAT                              = 7943,  -- It was twenty years ago, during the Grrreat War, when the walls were destroyed and the place became flooded. But betterrr to have an abundance of waterrr than none at all, eh?
        WHEN_I_WAS_JUST_A_KITTEN_THE_STAR                                       = 7944,  -- When I was just a kitten, the Star Sibyl came out and gave a speech to everrrybody.
        SHE_SAID_TWO_THINGS_THAT_WE_SHOULD_ALL                                  = 7945,  -- She said two things: that we should all play nice with the beastmen, and that nobody could use summonimoning magic anymorrre. What's summonimoning magic?
        I_M_LOOKING_FOR_BADDIE_WADDIES_WHEN_I                                   = 7946,  -- I'm looking for baddie-waddies. When I catch 'em, I throw 'em in a scary-wary jail.
        YOU_RE_NOT_DOING_ANYTHING_BAD_ARE_YOU                                   = 7947,  -- You're not doing anything bad, are you? If you are, you have to tell me, you know!
        I_M_SURE_YOU_VE_SEEN_THE_AUTOMATON                                      = 7948,  -- I'm sure you've seen the automaton guards positioned all around Windurrrst. You had better take carrre when dealing with those Cardians.
        THIS_IS_JUST_BETWEEN_YOU_AND_ME_BUT                                     = 7949,  -- This is just between you and me, but those machines go crrrazy sometimes. I've even heard that there have been Tarutaru kidnapped by the malfunctioning Carrrdians!
        HISS_GET_OUT_OF_HERRRE                                                  = 7950,  -- <Hiss!> Get out of herrre.
        WE_KIDS_KEEP_OUR_TAILS_OUT_OF_YOU                                       = 7951,  -- We kids keep our tails out of you adults' business, so you keep your big noses out of ourrrs!
        NOT_ONLY_THE_STAR_SIBYL_LIVES_IN_HEAVENS                                = 7952,  -- Not only the Star Sibyl lives in Heavens Towerrr. Her ladies-in-waiting and the Mithra Sibyl Guards also serrrve her there.
        OUT_OF_ALL_THE_GUARDS_PROTECTING_THE_STAR                               = 7953,  -- Out of all the guards protecting the Star Sibyl, Semih Lafihna is the most powerrrful. And why shouldn't she be? She is the only Mithra worrrthy enough to accept our chieftainness's bow.
        I_CAME_HERRRE_TO_GIVE_THAT_STAR_SIBYL                                   = 7954,  -- I came herrre to give that Star Sibyl a piece of my mind! Why do we have to be frrriends with those filthy Yagudo?
        THEY_CONTINUE_RRRAVAGING_THE_COUNTRYSIDE_JUST_BECAUSE_NO                = 7955,  -- They continue rrravaging the countryside just because no one herrre in Windurst has the guts to stand up to them!
        TWENTY_YEARRRS_AGO_THE_ALLIED_FORRRCES_SUCCEEDED_IN                     = 7956,  -- Twenty yearrrs ago, the allied forrrces succeeded in defeating the lord of the beastmen. Howeverrr, they were not able to take the beastman forces out completely.
        IF_WINDURST_HAD_ONLY_A_LITTLE_MORE_POWERRR                              = 7957,  -- If Windurst had only a little more powerrr then, we could have taken care of our birrrd problem, and there would be no need to fake a happy coexistence with the Yagudo.
        GNYAH_HA_HA_WHAT_A_MIGHTY_QUEER_COUNTRY                                 = 7958,  -- Gnyah ha ha! What a mighty queer country this here Windurst is! The people are smaller than dogs and the trees are as big as mountains.
        AND_THAT_BIG_HONKIN_THING_OVER_YONDER_THEY                              = 7959,  -- And that big honkin' thing over yonder... They say that some star-lady is all living up in there. I wonder if she's into sophisty-cated guys like yours truly.
        IT_S_JUST_LOVELY_HERE_AWAY_FROM_THE                                     = 7960,  -- It's just lovely here, away from the smoke and bustle of Bastok. Take a deep breath and smell that fresh air.
        WHENEVER_I_NEED_TO_RELAX_I_JUST_KICK                                    = 7961,  -- Whenever I need to relax, I just kick back and take in the scenery.
        I_HEARD_FROM_THAT_CONSULATE_OVER_THERE_THAT                             = 7962,  -- I heard from that consulate over there that Windurst has formed a peace pact with the Yagudo.
        CAN_YOU_BELIEVE_IT_HAVE_THEY_ALREADY_FORGOT                             = 7963,  -- Can you believe it? Have they already forgot what happened twenty years ago?
        HMM_I_WAS_JUST_TALKING_TO_AROMU_OROMU                                   = 7964,  -- Hmm... I was just talking to Aromu-Oromu here about the Windurstian government.
        CAN_YOU_BELIEVE_THAT_ALL_THE_GOINGS_ON                                  = 7965,  -- Can you believe that all the goings-on in this country are decided by the Star Sibyl's fortune-telling? They say that it's tradition, but I just don't see the logic in it...
        HOWDY_DOWDY_YOU_RE_IN_WINDURST_WALLS_BUDDY                              = 7966,  -- Howdy-dowdy! You're in Windurst Walls, buddy/missy]. I can warp you to Port Windurst if you want me to!
        WARP_TO_PORT_WINDURST_YES_NO                                            = 7967,  -- Warp to Port Windurst? Yes. No.
        HAVE_YOU_ALREADY_BEEN_INSIDE_HEAVENS_TOWER_I                            = 7968,  -- Have you already been inside Heavens Tower? I came all the way here to see this strange spring inside. They say you can see the stars in it.
        THE_STAR_READING_CEREMONY_IS_A_SPECIAL_RITE_2                           = 7969,  -- The Star Reading ceremony is a special rite that entails the gathering of the five ministers and the Star Sibyl together to listen-wisten to the will of the stars in the skies above.
        THE_LAST_FEW_YEARS_STAR_READING_WEADINGS_DIDN                           = 7970,  -- The last few years' Star Reading-weadings didn't say much either way...neither good omens, nor bad.
