        AND_ON_TOP_OF_THAT_WHAT_ABOUT_THIS                                      = 11162,  -- And on top of that, what about this Caboose-ethy!? It went on a rampage trying to destroy all living things, yet a handful of beastmen-ethy were able to stop it!
        HEARING_THAT_CABOOSE_WAS_DEFEATED_FIVE_THOUSAND_YEARS                   = 11163,  -- Hearing that Caboose was defeated five thousand years ago makes my eyes all teary. This could've been our chance to complete the maelstrom theory.
        DOCTOR_SHANTOTTO_HAVE_YOU_FORGOTTEN_THAT_TALK_ETHY                      = 11164,  -- Doctor Shantotto, have you forgotten that talk-ethy of the maelstrom theory has been banned? Isn't simply being involved with such a book-ethy an act of treason?
        EVERYONE_RE_RIDDLY_MAIN_CALM_ALSO_IT_S                                  = 11165,  -- Everyone, re-riddly-main calm. Also, it's Chaos, not Caboose.
        MOREOVER_THIS_ADVENTURER_EENO_IS_CLEARLY_CONFUSED_ABOUT                 = 11166,  -- Moreover, this adventurer-eeno is clearly confused about a variety of things-areeno.
        THERE_IS_A_GOOD_CHANCE_THAT_MUCH_AROO                                   = 11167,  -- There is a good chance that much-aroo like us, he/she] is under the influence of Uran-Mafran's memory manipulation madiddly-magic.
        OOH_MEMORIES_STOLEN                                                     = 11168,  -- Ooh... Memories...stolen...
        LOOK_MEMORIAN_IS_REACTING_JUST_AREENO_AS_I                              = 11169,  -- Look, Memorian is reacting just-areeno as I anticipated.
        HUH_DOES_THAT_MEAN_THERE_MIGHT_BE_MORE                                  = 11170,  -- Huh!? Does that mean there might be more to learn? And here I thought there was no more to discern.
        IT_CERTAINLY_DOES_MEAN_AREENO_THAT_HERE_I                               = 11171,  -- It certainly does mean-areeno that. Here, I'll give this madiddly-magic doll to you.
        IT_SHOULD_RE_RIDDILY_ACT_TO_THE_MEMORIES                                = 11172,  -- It should re-riddily-act to the memories that were tampered with by Uran-Mafran and then remove the effects of his spell-areeno.
        WHEN_YOU_HAVE_A_MOMENT_AREENO_YOU_SHOULD                                = 11173,  -- When you have a moment-areeno, you should try visiting locations-aroo that you have been to before.
        IF_YOU_FIND_ANYTHING_REGARDING_THE_MAELSTROM_THEORY                     = 11174,  -- %, if you find anything regarding the maelstrom theory, come to me at once. That is not the kind of information that should be shared with a mere dunce.
        NO_YOU_SHOULD_TELL_ME_ETHY_OR_PROFESSOR                                 = 11175,  -- No, you should tell me-ethy or Professor Koru-Moru first. It is vital that any buds of rebellion-ethy are plucked before they can sprout.
        PROFESSOR_YORAN_ORAN_I_NEED_TO_EXAMINE_THE                              = 11176,  -- Professor Yoran-Oran, I need to examine the maelstrom theory. In order to understand the Maelstrom Mage, I must pore over it until my eyes are tired and bleary.
        IF_URAN_MAFRAN_S_MEMORIES_EVER_RE_RIDDILY                               = 11177,  -- If Uran-Mafran's memories ever re-riddily-return, I'd like to capture and question-areeno him.
        YES_I_WHOLEHEARTEDLY_AGREE_THIS_IS_NO_TIME                              = 11178,  -- Yes, I wholeheartedly agree. This is no time for me to squabble with thee.
        WE_MUST_GET_TO_THE_BOTTOM_OF_THESE                                      = 11179,  -- We must get to the bottom of these mysteries before Uran-Mafran returns. Then we can see just how brightly this plot burns.
        FINALLY_I_WOULD_LIKE_TO_GIVE_YOU_THIS                                   = 11180,  -- Finally, %, I would like to give you this. If I let you leave without it, I would certainly be remiss.
        I_BELIEVE_IT_WILL_HELP_YOU_ON_YOUR                                      = 11181,  -- I believe it will help you on your journey to restore your memories. Be sure to keep it with your most prized accessories.
        IT_IS_ALWAYS_GOOD_TO_PREPARE_FOR_THE                                    = 11182,  -- It is always good to prepare for the worst. Now then, I think you should visit the Kingdom of San d'Oria first.
        PRINCE_TRION_HAS_BEEN_QUITE_VOCAL_ABOUT_VARIOUS                         = 11183,  -- Prince Trion has been quite vocal about various things. Especially regarding what kind of power the World Eater Egg brings.
        OF_COURSE_THERE_IS_NO_NEED_TO_MENTION                                   = 11184,  -- Of course, there is no need to mention the maelstrom theory. If you do, you will not find my mood to be so cheery.
        THE_MAELSTROM_THEORY_IS_A_FORBIDDEN_BOOK_SO                             = 11185,  -- The maelstrom theory is a forbidden book, so you can be charged with treason. And I won't really care if you have a good reason!
        IS_THIS_ANOTHER_SIDE_EFFECT_THAT_URAN_MAFRAN                            = 11186,  -- Is this another side effect that Uran-Mafran's memory manipulation has brought? Here, take this % that you forgot.
        I_M_TOLD_THAT_YOU_SHOULD_TAKE_THE                                       = 11187,  -- I'm told that you should take the magic doll modified by Professor Koru-Moru as well. Maybe it can help break through Uran-Mafran's spell.
        IF_YOU_HAVE_NO_SET_DESTINATION_IN_MIND                                  = 11188,  -- If you have no set destination in mind, head for the Kingdom of San d'Oria before your memory's completely in tatters. Prince Trion seems to be quite curious about a variety of interesting matters.
        YOU_SHOULD_TRY_TO_MEET_WITH_HIM_SOON                                    = 11189,  -- You should try to meet with him soon. Otherwise, he's likely to put on a disguise and sneak out of the country at the next full moon.
        UMM_THIS_ISN_T_GOOD_AREENO_I_M                                          = 11190,  -- Umm... This isn't good-areeno... I'm trying to riddly-recall my time as minister in order to remember-aroo Uran-Mafran's weakness...
        THERE_MUST_HAVE_BEEN_AT_LEAST_ONE_STUDENT                               = 11191,  -- There must have been at least one student-aroo he was close with, but I can't recollect the name. I know he was male though... Yes, definitely male-areeno.
        THE_MAELSTROM_MAGE_GARAZU_HOREIZU_DIED_DURING_THE                       = 11192,  -- The Maelstrom Mage, Garazu-Horeizu, died during the Fourth Yagudo War, and his soul-ethy was summoned by the demon and invited to Valhalla.
        THEN_OVER_THE_COURSE_OF_HUNDREDS_OF_YEARS                               = 11193,  -- Then, over the course of hundreds of years, he completed his maelstrom theory-ethy and acquired a source of inexhaustible magical power, enabling him to launch a rebellion-ethy against Odin.
        BASED_ON_OUR_CURRENT_ASSUMPTIONS_IS_SUCH_A                              = 11194,  -- Based on our current assumptions, is such a thing possible-ethy, even when considering his vast intellect-ethy?
        AH_IT_S_YOU_YOUR_FACE_APPEARS_TO                                        = 11195,  -- Ah, it's you. Your face appears to be rather fresh and true.
        YOU_LOOK_AS_IF_A_GREAT_WEIGHT_HAS                                       = 11196,  -- You look as if a great weight has been lifted from your heart. Yes, your aura has brightened considerably since I saw you last depart.
        ARRRRRRG_IT_S_OVER_IT_S_ALL_OVER                                        = 11197,  -- Arrrrrrg... It's over... It's all over...
        OH_IT_SEEMS_THAT_MAGIC_DOLL_HAS_SERVED                                  = 11198,  -- Oh, it seems that magic doll has served its purpose at last. Now we can put its sinister visage in the past.
        VERY_WELL_WHAT_HAPPENS_NEXT_ONLY_TIME_WILL                              = 11199,  -- Very well. What happens next, only time will tell.
        NOW_THAT_IT_S_ALL_OVER_THIS_MAGIC                                       = 11200,  -- Now that it's all over, this magic doll is kind of cute, I must say... On second thought, I take that back. Clearly, the influence of Koru-Moru is still at play.
        THIS_IS_AN_EXPLANATION_OF_THE_ASSIST_CHANNEL                            = 11201,  -- This is an explanation of the Assist Channel feature, which allows new and returning players to seek help from veteran adventurers.
        YOU_MUST_TAKE_ON_THE_RECORDS_OF_EMINENCE                                = 11202,  -- You must take on the % Records of Eminence objective before receiving the explanation.
        YOU_MUST_COMPLETE_BEFORE_TAKING_ON_THE_RECORDS                          = 11203,  -- You must complete % before taking on the % Records of Eminence objective.
        WHAT_DO_YOU_WANT_TO_LEARN_ABOUT_WHAT                                    = 11204,  -- What do you want to learn about? What is the Assist Channel? How can I post a message? What are the requirements? Where can I access it? Tell me about mentor messages. Where can I find mentors? What are Thumbs Up and Warnings? What happens if I am muted? When do my posting rights expire? Nothing for now.
        THE_ASSIST_CHANNEL_IS_A_SPECIAL_CHAT_CHANNEL                            = 11205,  -- The Assist Channel is a special chat channel that allows adventurers to ask questions and receive advice from veteran players known as mentors.
        PRESS_THE_SPACE_BAR_TO_BRING_UP_THE                                     = 11206,  -- Press the space bar to bring up the text window at the bottom of the screen and type /assistj (your message) or /assiste (your message) to post your message.
        YOU_CAN_ALSO_USE_AJ_FOR_ASSISTJ_AND                                     = 11207,  -- You can also use /aj for /assistj, and /ae for /assiste.
        ADDITIONALLY_PRESSING_CTRL_Q_WILL_DISPLAY_ASSISTJ_OR                    = 11208,  -- Additionally, pressing CTRL+Q will display /assistj or /assiste in the text window for you.
        YOU_CAN_CHANGE_THE_CTRL_Q_SHORTCUT_COMMAND                              = 11209,  -- You can change the CTRL+Q shortcut command...
        BY_GOING_TO_MAIN_MENU_CONFIG_MISC_2                                     = 11210,  -- ...by going to Main Menu > Config > Misc. 2 > Key Assignment > Commands > Chat: /AssistE or /AssistJ.
        IT_IS_RECOMMENDED_THAT_YOU_USE_ASSISTJ_AJ                               = 11211,  -- It is recommended that you use /assistj (/aj) when posting in Japanese, and /assiste (/ae) when posting in English.
        YOU_MUST_MEET_ONE_OF_THE_FOLLOWING_CONDITIONS                           = 11212,  -- You must meet one of the following conditions in order to post to the Assist Channel.
        ID_1_YOU_ARE_A_NEW_PLAYER_YOU_MAY                                       = 11213,  -- 1. You are a new player You may post messages from the moment you first set foot in Vana'diel.
        ID_2_YOU_ARE_A_RETURNEE_AS_A_RETURNING                                  = 11214,  -- 2. You are a returnee As a returning player, you may post messages upon logging in with a character that has not logged in for at least 48 days.
        ID_3_YOU_ARE_A_MENTOR_YOU_MAY_POST                                      = 11215,  -- 3. You are a mentor You may post messages as long as you remain a mentor to other players.
        NEW_PLAYERS_AND_RETURNEES_MAY_POST_MESSAGES_UNTIL                       = 11216,  -- New players and returnees may post messages until they have been logged in for a total of 48 hours since first receiving their posting rights.
        IF_YOU_WISH_TO_CHECK_HOW_LONG_YOU                                       = 11217,  -- If you wish to check how long you can continue to post for, speak to an and choose "When do my posting rights expire?" to see how much time you have left.
        THE_ASSIST_CHANNEL_CAN_ONLY_BE_USED_IN                                  = 11218,  -- The Assist Channel can only be used in the following areas.
        AVAILABLE_AREAS                                                         = 11219,  -- Available areas: %, %, %, %, %, %...
        ID_11220                                                                = 11220,  -- ...%, %, %, %, %, %, %, %...
        ID_11221                                                                = 11221,  -- ...%, %, %, %, %, %, %, %...
        AND_YOUR_MOG_HOUSE_RENT_A_ROOM                                          = 11222,  -- ...%, %, %, and your Mog House (Rent-a-Room).
        YOU_CANNOT_POST_OR_READ_MESSAGES_OUTSIDE_OF                             = 11223,  -- You cannot post or read messages outside of the areas listed above.
        EVEN_IN_AREAS_WHERE_MESSAGES_ARE_ALLOWED_YOU                            = 11224,  -- Even in areas where messages are allowed, you cannot post consecutive messages. Please wait a while after posting a message.
        MENTOR_MESSAGES_ARE_ACCOMPANIED_BY_A_FLAG_O                             = 11225,  -- Mentor messages are accompanied by a flag (o/) marker. This marker indicates the mentor's reliability (Mentor Class) and experience as an adventurer (Mastery Rank).
        AS_A_MENTOR_S_MENTOR_CLASS_INCREASES_THE                                = 11226,  -- As a mentor's Mentor Class increases, the color and shape of the marker will change: o/ > o9 > oC
        A_OC_MARKER_IS_A_SIGN_THAT_THE                                          = 11227,  -- A oC marker is a sign that the mentor has earned the highest levels of trust from other adventurers.
        THE_NUMBER_AFFIXED_TO_THE_MARKER_IS_THE                                 = 11228,  -- The number affixed to the marker is the mentor's Mastery Rank, and indicates how experienced the mentor is as an adventurer.
        THE_HIGHER_THE_NUMBER_THE_MORE_EXPERIENCED_THE                          = 11229,  -- The higher the number, the more experienced the mentor is.
        YOU_CAN_CHECK_YOUR_OWN_MASTERY_RANK_EVEN                                = 11230,  -- You can check your own Mastery Rank even if you do not serve as a mentor, so feel free to take a look every now and then if you are curious.
        YOU_CAN_CHECK_YOUR_MASTERY_RANK_BY_GOING                                = 11231,  -- You can check your Mastery Rank by going to Main Menu > Status > Profile.
        IF_YOU_WISH_TO_SPEAK_DIRECTLY_TO_A                                      = 11232,  -- If you wish to speak directly to a mentor, you can search for mentors by going to Main Menu > Help Desk > Mentor Search.
        THE_THUMBS_UP_FEATURE_ENABLES_YOU_TO_LET                                = 11233,  -- The Thumbs Up feature enables you to let mentors know when their comments proved to be especially helpful.
        MENTORS_WHO_EARN_LOTS_OF_THUMBS_UP_REPLIES                              = 11234,  -- Mentors who earn lots of Thumbs Up replies from other adventurers will see their Mentor Class increase.
        REMEMBER_TO_GIVE_A_THUMBS_UP_TO_ANY                                     = 11235,  -- Remember to give a Thumbs Up to any mentor you feel helped you out or taught you something useful.
        A_WARNING_IS_A_FEATURE_THAT_CAN_ONLY                                    = 11236,  -- A Warning is a feature that can only be used by mentors.
        PLEASE_USE_THIS_FEATURE_WHEN_A_POST_S                                   = 11237,  -- Please use this feature when a post's contents are insufficient or otherwise may be construed as harassment.
        TO_SEND_A_THUMBS_UP_OR_WARNING_TO                                       = 11238,  -- To send a Thumbs Up or Warning to another player, open the Chat Log Window and move the cursor over the relevant message and press the confirm button (Enter key) to bring up the evaluation menu.
        EVALUATIONS_CAN_BE_MADE_FOR_10_MINUTES_FOLLOWING                        = 11239,  -- Evaluations can be made for 10 minutes following the designated player's latest post to the Assist Channel.
        YOU_MAY_SEND_UP_TO_ONE_THUMBS_UP                                        = 11240,  -- You may send up to one Thumbs Up and one Warning per day (Earth time).
        THE_MUTE_FEATURE_PLACES_RESTRICTIONS_ON_YOUR_ABILITY                    = 11241,  -- The Mute feature places restrictions on your ability to post, meaning that other players will be unable to see the messages you post to the Assist Channel.
        PLEASE_REFRAIN_FROM_POSTING_UNSUITABLE_CONTENT_SO_THAT                  = 11242,  -- Please refrain from posting unsuitable content so that the veteran adventurers are not forced to mute you.
        MUTE_STATUS_CAN_BE_REMOVED_BY_PLAYERS_THAT                              = 11243,  -- Mute status can be removed by players that have the necessary Mute List access rights, or it will be removed automatically 24 hours (Earth time) after the mute status was enabled.
        YOU_ARE_FREE_TO_POST_MESSAGES_TO_THE                                    = 11244,  -- You are free to post messages to the Assist Channel until you decide to stop serving as a mentor.
        YOU_MAY_POST_MESSAGES_TO_THE_ASSIST_CHANNEL                             = 11245,  -- You may post messages to the Assist Channel until : on //. (Time remaining: Approx. # [sec./min./hr.])
        IF_YOU_LOG_OUT_WHILE_YOU_STILL_HAVE                                     = 11246,  -- If you log out while you still have time available, your remaining time will be carried over to the next time you log in.
        YOU_ARE_ABOUT_TO_LOSE_THE_ABILITY_TO                                    = 11247,  -- You are about to lose the ability to post messages to the Assist Channel.
        YOU_ARE_UNABLE_TO_POST_MESSAGES_TO_THE                                  = 11248,  -- You are unable to post messages to the Assist Channel.
        TAKE_ON_THE_RECORDS_OF_EMINENCE_OBJECTIVE_FROM                          = 11249,  -- Take on the % Records of Eminence objective from the Tutorial section of the Records of Eminence Menu and speak to the A.M.A.N. liaison.
        FAIR_GREETINGS_TO_YOU_WANDERER_I_AM_A                                   = 11250,  -- Fair greetings to you, wanderer. I am a linkshell concierge, charged with uniting lone explorers of Vana'diel with linkshells of similar goals.
        HOW_MAY_I_HELP_YOU_TODAY                                                = 11251,  -- How may I help you today?
        WHAT_DO_YOU_DESIRE_NOTHING_FOR_NOW_SHOW                                 = 11252,  -- What do you desire? Nothing for now. Show me recruiting linkshells. I'd like to hand out %. Tell me more. Open up the linkshell window.
        IT_WAS_MY_PLEASURE_TO_MEET_WITH_YOU                                     = 11253,  -- It was my pleasure to meet with you this fine day. May you encounter many friendly faces throughout your travels.
        EXCELLENT_PLEASE_SELECT_WHICH_LINKSHELL_YOU_ARE_INTERESTED              = 11254,  -- Excellent. Please select which linkshell you are interested in contacting.
        ARE_YOU_CERTAIN                                                         = 11255,  -- Are you certain?
        REALLY_RECEIVE_THE_LINKPEARL_OF_COURSE_NO_THANK                         = 11256,  -- Really receive the linkpearl? Of course. No, thank you.
        IN_THE_INTEREST_OF_FAIRNESS_I_AM_UNABLE                                 = 11257,  -- In the interest of fairness, I am unable to distribute multiple linkpearls to someone on the same day. Please come back tomorrow.
        IT_IS_MY_SINCERE_PLEASURE_TO_BESTOW_THIS                                = 11258,  -- It is my sincere pleasure to bestow this upon you.
        YOUR_NEW_LINKSHELL_IS_BEYOND_DOUBT_FILLED_WITH                          = 11259,  -- Your new linkshell is beyond doubt filled with many looking for new companions. Be sure to say a few words of greeting.
        I_HAVE_PREPARED_A_SMALL_MANUAL_DESCRIBING_THE                           = 11260,  -- I have prepared a small manual describing the importance of treating others with respect. Please have a quick glance at it when you have a moment.
        MAY_YOUR_NEW_LINKSHELL_PROVIDE_YOU_WITH_FOND                            = 11261,  -- May your new linkshell provide you with fond memories that will last a lifetime.
        THOUGH_IT_PAINS_ME_TO_SAY_THIS_I                                        = 11262,  -- Though it pains me to say this, I have no % that meet your requirements at this time.
        SHOULD_YOU_DESIRE_I_CAN_CANCEL_YOUR_REGISTRATION                        = 11263,  -- Should you desire, I can cancel your registration.
        CANCEL_REGISTRATION_YES_PLEASE_NOT_AT_THIS_TIME                         = 11264,  -- Cancel registration? Yes, please. Not at this time.
        SHOULD_YOU_DESIRE_TO_LOOK_FOR_MEMBERS_I                                 = 11265,  -- Should you desire to look for members, I can distribute % in your stead by utilizing the energies continued within your equipped %.
        DURING_THE_PROCESS_PLEASE_EQUIP_EITHER_OR_AS                            = 11266,  -- During the process, please equip either % or % as Linkshell 1 and select I'd like to hand out %.
        ONE_THAT_STEP_HAS_BEEN_COMPLETED_I_WILL                                 = 11267,  -- One that step has been completed, I will ask you a series of questions.
        TO_CANCEL_YOUR_REGISTRATION_EQUIP_OR_AS_LINKSHELL                       = 11268,  -- To cancel your registration, equip % or % as Linkshell 1, speak to me again, and select the appropriate linkshell from the list.
        UNFORTUNATELY_ONLY_THOSE_EQUIPPED_WITH_OR_AS_LINKSHELL                  = 11269,  -- Unfortunately, only those equipped with % or % as Linkshell 1 are able to distribute %.
        ONCE_IN_A_LIFETIME_MEETINGS_MAKE_FOR_WONDERFUL                          = 11270,  -- Once-in-a-lifetime meetings make for wonderful stories, but no treasure can compare to being part of a group of friends you can call home.
        LINKSHELL_CONCIERGES_SUCH_AS_MYSELF_BRING_TOGETHER_ADVENTURERS          = 11271,  -- Linkshell concierges such as myself bring together adventurers of similar interests.
        IN_A_WORD_WE_MATCH_ADVENTURERS_LOOKING_FOR                              = 11272,  -- In a word, we match adventurers looking for linkshells with those linkshells interested in taking in new members.
        I_ACCEPT_FROM_LINKSHELLS_THE_WORLD_OVER_AND                             = 11273,  -- I accept % from linkshells the world over and distribute them to appropriate adventurers.
        THIS_SERVICE_IS_PROVIDED_BY_THE_ADVENTURERS_MUTUAL                      = 11274,  -- This service is provided by the Adventurers' Mutual Aid Network, and as such, anyone working for Vana'diel's greater good is eligible to participate.
        ADDITIONALLY_PLEASE_BE_AWARE_THAT_I_AM_ONLY                             = 11275,  -- Additionally, please be aware that I am only able to offer you one % per day.
        THOUGH_WE_WOULD_LIKE_TO_OFFER_THIS_SERVICE                              = 11276,  -- Though we would like to offer this service free of charge, the network has its own expenses that must be paid, so we charge a nominal fee of # gil at the time of registration.
        IT_IS_ALSO_WORTH_NOTING_THAT_CAN_ONLY                                   = 11277,  -- It is also worth noting that % can only be registered by adventurers who have been active in Vana'diel for at least # days (Earth time).
        IT_IS_WORTH_NOTING_THAT_EACH_CONCIERGE_MAY                              = 11278,  -- It is worth noting that each concierge may only register a maximum of # linkshells.
        ONCE_THE_NUMBER_OF_REGISTRATIONS_HAS_HIT_THE                            = 11279,  -- Once the number of registrations has hit the limit, existing registrations will be canceled in order of oldest to newest.
        SERVER_MAINTENANCES_WILL_ALSO_IMMEDIATELY_CANCEL_ALL_REGISTRATIONS      = 11280,  -- Server maintenances will also immediately cancel all registrations, so be sure to keep your information up-to-date.
        THANK_YOU_FOR_TAKING_THE_TIME_TO_USE                                    = 11281,  -- Thank you for taking the time to use our service. Let me confirm the information contained within.
        CORRECT                                                                 = 11282,  -- , correct?
        LS0                                                                     = 11283,  -- LS0: .
        LS1                                                                     = 11284,  -- LS1: .
        LS0_NO_SENDING                                                          = 11285,  -- LS0: (No sending).
        LS1_NO_SENDING                                                          = 11286,  -- LS1: (No sending).
        SHALL_I_START_LOOKING_FOR_NEW_MEMBERS_FOR                               = 11287,  -- Shall I start looking for new members for a fee of # gil?
        LOOK_FOR_NEW_MEMBERS_GIL_THAT_SOUNDS_WONDERFUL                          = 11288,  -- Look for new members? (# gil) That sounds wonderful. I'd rather not.
        I_M_QUITE_SORRY_TO_HEAR_YOU_DECLINE                                     = 11289,  -- I'm quite sorry to hear you decline. Please let me know if you change your mind.
        I_WILL_NOW_ASK_YOU_A_SERIES_OF                                          = 11290,  -- I will now ask you a series of questions about your preferences. Be sure to answer truthfully so that you can find new members that match your style.
        WHAT_IS_YOUR_LANGUAGE_PREFERENCE_JAPANESE_ENGLISH_OTHER                 = 11291,  -- What is your language preference? Japanese. English. Other. Back.
        WHAT_DAYS_ARE_YOU_MOST_ACTIVE_EVERY_DAY                                 = 11292,  -- What days are you most active? Every day. Weekends and holidays. Weekdays. Monday. Tuesday. Wednesday. Thursday. Friday. Saturday. Sunday. Back.
        WHAT_DAYS_ARE_YOU_MOST_ACTIVE_NO_DAY                                    = 11293,  -- What days are you most active? [-/Z]No day set. [-/Z]Mondays. [-/Z]Tuesdays. [-/Z]Wednesdays. [-/Z]Thursdays. [-/Z]Fridays. [-/Z]Saturdays. [-/Z]Sundays. [-/Z]Holidays. Back. Next. Update.
        WHEN_DO_YOU_PLAYING_ON_NO_TIME_SET                                      = 11294,  -- When do you [start/stop] playing on [weekdays/weekends]? No time set. 12:00 a.m. 1:00 a.m.:00 a.m.:00 a.m. 4:00 a.m. 5:00 a.m. 6:00 a.m. 7:00 a.m. 8:00 a.m. 9:00 a.m. 10:00 a.m. 11:00 a.m. 12:00 p.m. 1:00 p.m.:00 p.m.:00 p.m. 4:00 p.m. 5:00 p.m. 6:00 p.m. 7:00 p.m. 8:00 p.m. 9:00 p.m. 10:00 p.m. 11:00 p.m. Back.
        DESIGNATE_A_TIME_ZONE_NO_DESIGNATION_JAPANESE_STANDARD                  = 11295,  -- Designate a time zone. No designation. Japanese Standard Time (JST). Pacific Time (PST|PDT). Greenwich Mean Time (GMT). Back.
        WHAT_TIME_ARE_YOU_ACTIVE_JST_IN_THE                                     = 11296,  -- What time are you active? (JST) In the morning. In the afternoon. In the evening. At night. In the wee hours of the morning. Return to previous selection.
        WHAT_TIME_ARE_YOU_ACTIVE_PST_PDT_IN                                     = 11297,  -- What time are you active? (PST|PDT) In the morning. In the afternoon. In the evening. At night. In the wee hours of the morning. Return to previous selection.
        WHAT_TIME_ARE_YOU_ACTIVE_GMT_IN_THE                                     = 11298,  -- What time are you active? (GMT) In the morning. In the afternoon. In the evening. At night. In the wee hours of the morning. Return to previous selection.
